        "subject": "LU-13737 lnet: Have lnetctl display discovered routes",
        "message": "LU-13737 lnet: Have lnetctl display discovered routes\n\nWhen discovery finds that a router is multi-rail it will consolidate\nany routes that are equivalent. This hides useful information about\nindividual route status. Modify the lnetctl route show command so\nthat it prints information about all routes through MR gateways.\n\nThis change also moves the route state into the default output\nrather than verbose.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9065\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I7bf20b0a8a96db2b5807d297cc37291ebeeca53f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
